label: Fundamental Organic Chem II
description: Course is the second term of a two-term integrated sequence and should be taken the term following enrollment in CHEM 236. Additional fees may apply. See Class Schedule. 3 undergraduate hours. 3 graduate hours. Credit is not given for both CHEM 436 and CHEM 332. Prerequisite: CHEM 236 and CHEM 237; or CHEM 232 and CHEM 233 with consent of instructor.
